<div id="review_3516145788" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3516145788" />
    <a title="Danie Ware" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2283876-danie-ware"><img alt="Danie Ware" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1553420120p2/2283876.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3516145788?book_show_action=true">Oct 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Danie Ware" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Danie Ware" href="/user/show/2283876-danie-ware">Danie Ware</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3516145788" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17265260759549221234">This isn’t a story, it’s an extended and somewhat windy episode of a soap opera. Was wonderful to see my youthful friends again and to see who they’d become, but a lack of anything resembling a narrative structure, some very sketchy and clumsily nailed-on sub-plots, plus a couple of holes you could have flown a dragon through... yeah. Nice to take a peek back at my youth, and worth the read to find that final closure, but kind of a struggle to finish.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


