<div id="review_3857340041" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3857340041" />
    <a title="Richard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11138857-richard"><img alt="Richard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1342835081p2/11138857.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3857340041?book_show_action=true">Feb 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Richard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Richard" href="/user/show/11138857-richard">Richard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3857340041" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5079331189278307665">Another re-read. Aside from the characters (who I know from the other books in the series), this is a great study in how new technological advances affect a society. The fact that the author could weave that into a fantasy world so convincingly is very impressive.<br/><br/>There are some things in the world of Pern that I don&apos;t particularly like, but there are things in this world that I don&apos;t particularly like. It&apos;s a good series.</span>
  <span id="freeText5079331189278307665" style="display:none">Another re-read. Aside from the characters (who I know from the other books in the series), this is a great study in how new technological advances affect a society. The fact that the author could weave that into a fantasy world so convincingly is very impressive.<br /><br />There are some things in the world of Pern that I don't particularly like, but there are things in this world that I don't particularly like. It's a good series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5079331189278307665" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


